<div class="leftblock">

    <h2>All of our real time dust sampling and monitoring equipment is MCERTS accredited</h2>  
    <h1>Air quality surveys</h1>
    <p>Air Quality Survey reports can be created from data gathered by routine monitoring in conjunction with weather sensors which can also be included to measure wind speed and direction, which can also be used to demonstrate adequate environmental and safety controls during demolition or other dust creating projects, and configured to alert site operatives by sending a text message upon exceeding a predetermined limit based on a prior survey of the ambient air quality in an area.</p>
    <h2>Gravimetric dust sampling</h2>
    <p>Gravimetric dust sampling is also available, to collect physical samples of airborne particles for analysis of their chemical composition.</p>
    <p>We have static monitors which can analyse samples from an area over time, or personal monitoring equipment which can collect data on the individual exposure to dust of operatives whilst carrying out site activities.</p>
    <h2>Settleable dust sampling</h2>
    <p>We also offer settleable dust sampling using frisbee type dust collectors. Samples are usually collected several weeks apart to allow dust to settle.</p>
    <p>Samples can be analysed to determine their composition.</p>
</div>